The average rate of change of C from x=10 to x=15 is

\[
\frac{C(15)-C(10)}{15-10}
=\frac{(15^2-4\cdot15+1000)-(10^2-4\cdot10+1000)}{5}
=\frac{(225-60+1000)-(100-40+1000)}{5}
=\frac{1165-1060}{5}
=\frac{105}{5}
=21.
\]

So the cost is increasing on average by \$21 per additional phone in that interval.

