=\;4\,\frac{x^2 - a^2}{(3 - x^2)(3 - a^2)}.
\]
Hence
\[
\frac{f(x)-f(a)}{x-a}
=4\,\frac{x^2 - a^2}{(3 - x^2)(3 - a^2)}\;\cdot\;\frac{1}{x - a}
=4\,\frac{(x-a)(x+a)}{(3 - x^2)(3 - a^2)}\;\cdot\;\frac{1}{x - a}
=-4\,\frac{x+a}{(3 - x^2)(3 - a^2)}.
\]
Now take the limit \(x\to a\):
\[
f'(a)=\lim_{x\to a}\frac{f(x)-f(a)}{x-a}
=-4\,\frac{a+a}{(3 - a^2)(3 - a^2)}
=-\frac{8a}{(3 - a^2)^2}.
\]
Thus the derivative is  
\[
\boxed{f'(x)=-\frac{8x}{\bigl(3 - x^2\bigr)^2}.}
\]
